verbose_text: Expression of ORF50 protein is required for expression of many KSHV encoded lytic genes such as K3, and K5 (homologs of the IE gene of BHV-4), viral interleukin-6 (vIL-6), viral macrophage inflammatory proteins (vMIPs), polyadenylated nuclear RNA (PAN), vBcl-2, K12, viral G-protein-coupled receptor (vGPCR), viral dihydrofolate reductase (vDHFR), DNA replication factors, and thymidylate synthase.
